,Not Recommended,486780,29729353,Posted: 5 February,all,Please Clap.,"Great game and a ton of polish, but it's missing one of the most important things for a vr game: the ability to not crash every time you exit. If you were to try and open another game after you're finished playing Fruit Ninja, the Vive headset fully shuts off and exits Steam VR. If you want to have ~ an hour long VR session, make sure this is the last game on your list.Other than that one fatal flaw, it's a great game and a ton of fun. I'd recommend putting one controller down, and double-handing only one sword. Feels much better, and makes you less likely to 'flail' your controllers in front of you hoping to hit everything."
